The paper describes the development of an artificial agent for financial risk and returns prediction using a modular cognitive system comprised of interconnected recurrent neural networks. This work involves machine learning, artificial intelligence, and computational finance, which are all covered by the arXiv categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). Additionally, the use of neural networks in the modular cognitive system suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the arXiv categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
